A 17-year-old youth has been charged in connection with disturbances in the Ardoyne area of Belfast on 13 July.The teenager is charged with possession of petrol bombs, throwing petrol bombs at police, riotous assembly and disorderly behaviour. He was arrested on Tuesday and is expected to appear before Belfast Youth Court on Wednesday. Shots were fired and petrol bombs thrown at police after the annual Twelfth parade passed through Ardoyne.